caption: It's simple but very good food for it's price range. The menu is a decent size in terms of variety for such a small place and is priced at a good range. Theyb offer some really good lunch specials as well more elaborated options for dinner.

Definitely not what it was in the late 80s and 90s....  read had zero flavor and chopped salad not much better. Should have know. That Saturday night at 6:30 pm walked in to 50% full on an already socially distanced restaurant.  Very disappointing....

Ordered the lasagna and cheese bread. That was possibly the blandest food I've ever eaten let alone the blandest lasagna I've ever eaten. And I grew up in the midwest, so I have an extensive knowledge of bland food. Had I been blindfolded the only indication that it was pasta I was eating would've come from the texture. Couldnt taste the meat, noodles, cheese, nor the sauce. Virtually tasteless, in its own way it was kind of impressive. The cheese bread is definitely not worth $8 either as it resembles  the frozen "New York garlic bread" bread stick if you were to cut it in half, then 6 piece and sprinkle cheese over the top. Even then the frozen breadsticks have more flavor.  I really hope their other dishes have more flavor.

From the moment you walk in, the settings great hospitality. The spices, the Alfredo sauce excellent. The noodles needed a little something. Toasted with a great bottle of wine,  music set the dinner. Thanks 👍

Ordered food online for pickup.   The service was quick and the food was delicious.   My only concern is the dining in part.  I Noticed a couple of customers walking in without a face mask on.  When I commented you need to be wearing a mask When entering the lady responded  “we are dining in So no face mask needed”.    I understood the city and county ordinance as that a face mask is required when entering and exiting a restaurant and may be removed when “actively eating” or when they sit down.  Walking to the restroom would warrant putting your face mask back on as well. Staff was busy preparing food and no one was monitoring customers entering their restaurant for adherence to safety protocol.

Wasn't to sure that getting curbside/takeout from an Italian place would be good. We got Lasagna and Spaghetti and Meatballs. All was AWESOME! super delicious. Can't wait till it opens for dine in - we will be back, Thanks for a great meal!

Ordered delivery through Postmates to our hotel during quarantine.  The seafood pasta, lasagna roll and Caesar salad had excellent flavor and were delivered at an appropriate temperature.   The portions were enough for at least two meals for two adults.  As part-time residents of Waikiki we look forward to visiting this restaurant in the future.

I and two friends went here tonight...first time for all of us...and we were certainly not disappointed! What a gem! First, service was prompt and courteous. Second, atmosphere was perfect (think Billy Joel's "Scenes from An Italian Restaurant"). Homey, but not hokey. Not over-the-top, but not too understated either.  Clean and comfortable.  Last,  but not least, the food! Two of us ordered the special...pasta of choice with a creamy pesto, spinach, broccoli, and topped with crispy bacon...! A generous portion and quite yummy yum yum! One of us ordered an appetizing, meaty pizza. This will be our favorite, regular meeting place for a long time to come!!  ...

My family and I had late dinner at the restaurant.  My son ordered meatballs on his pasta.  The meatballs were burnt and we told the waitress.  She took them back to the cook, the kitchen is open and you can see everything.  The cook cuts off the burnt parts, throws it back in a pan and recooks. My son gets parts of the meatballs to eat.  We paid for the burnt pieces, the waitress shrugged her shoulders and walked away.  It was late and my son just wanted to eat and go home. The quality is not the same,  we ate there often but not anymore.  The customers keep the business running.  The business depends on contact with the public.

Okay: Sausage Spaghetti noodles...not quite aldente, but not overcooked  Need to work on: Angel hair pasta was overcooked Service could be better  If I come back, I'll probably try their pizza...

Usually this place has great food and OK service.  This time it was good food and horrible & offending service.  Only 5 total tables of people the entire time I was there from the time we sat to the time we left.  Kind of sad for a Friday night.  The hostess was unpleasant and rushed to seat us so she could run back to her area and gonon her phone which she was on the whole night.  The waitress came to ask our drink order and my wife said diet Pepsi.  The waitress said 2 diet Pepsi's and I said yes I'll take a diet.  Then she said so 3 diets?  Made me think she was drunk.  I am a big guy and usually drink diet but I think she assumed I was getting a diet no matter what.  We then ordered an appetizer with the drinks.  5 minutes later we ordered our entrees.  15 minutes later our entrees came out and I asked about the appetizer and she said yes, one moment.  Then she came back a few minutes later and asked how the food was and said the appetizer is in the oven.  She forgot to put the appetizer order in, just apologize and move on.  At the end of the meal the appetizer came out.  The food was all good, I had the marsala chicken and the wife had chicken carbonara.  Halfway through the meal something started burning and smoke was filling the restaurant.   All the tables full of people, (all 3 of the tables) started looking around to make sure we were not in danger.  The smell and haze associated with burning food stayed the rest of the meal.  One table walked out witbout ordering thus resulting in loosing 30% of their customers.  I was upset they didn't ask if we still wanted the appetizer because it came out at the end of the meal.  I was upset and worried that they didn't address the burning, smoke and haze.  Last, everyone in there looked angry or unhappy to be at work.  Our waitress was nice, but she came off as either drunk or stupid and insensitive when assuming we both were getting diet drinks  Advice to management, hire better waitresses and hostesses.  They are supposed to be people people and nice.  If burning food happens often train staff to inform the patrons so they don't think there is a fire somewhere.

I came here many years ago and was it one of the best Italian restaurants I ever visited. However - new owners have missed the mark.  Terrible experience and I won't be visiting again.  Ordered the Ceasar salad, calamari appetizer and Chicken Parmesan a la vodka (which once upon a time was a trademark dish).  They didn't advertise a la vodka but they offered to make it when I ordered. I thought there was hope.  The Caesar salad was mediocre at best. Most likely store bought dressing with lettuce that was probably a day old. The salad had faint brown on its edges and has definitely been sitting for a while. The dressing was a little watery but flavorless. The croutons would have been a hit but a little soggy.  No ground pepper was offered.  The appetizer lacked the major player. The calamari. Plenty of onions, tomato and cheese and 12 pounds of butter buttttt three wedges of calamari.  The real disappointment was the entree. I basically got fried chicken tenders on fettuccini.  The a la vodka was anything but.  Very watered down but mostly flavorless.  The chicken batter was dark brown and slightly burnt. The meat was dry and flavorless.  The fettuccini was undercooked and I even showed the bright yellow and hard pasta to the waitress and she didn't have much input for resolution.  I ate the chicken fingers and the rest of the pasta went untouched.  The winner of it all was tho I didn't eat the pasta and even mentioned and showed it to the waitress - and I still got charged the extra fettuccine charge!!  I basically paid $30 for overcooked chicken fingers and a salad.  My suggestion is to find another Italian restaurant....... Way over priced and way underwhelming.

Excellent food and amazing staff!  The chef came out to ask how my meal was, which gave me the sense that he actually cares.  I ordered the chicken stuffed raviolis, and they were absolutely astounding!  Their drink specials were great, and their happy hour takes place when nearly no other establishments has one going on. The building itself is perfect for an Italian restaurant.  It reminds me of something that you'd see in a movie.  I had an amazing experience, and i will definitely be returning.

Summary:  food is good, service needs work but there's potential.  Parking is hit or miss.  Good food and selection of drinks.  Full bar and great happy hour specials.  Service needs work; two dishes from a party of four were delivered to the table, but the other two waiting over 15 minutes for a pizza and mushroom pasta. At least they comped the pizza though.  Initial wait for entree order was a bit slow too.  The kitchen is very loud and the dishwasher needs to learn how not to slam plates together when stacking them.

Took a while to get seated & when we finally did get a table we saw many other empty tables but we were seated by the restrooms. The place was poorly lit & it was HOT with only a few ceiling fans. When our waitress finally arrived she just stood there wait a blank look on her face. I had the corn chowder & it tasted like baby formula. The biggest disappointment was the pasta sauce which tasted like canned sauce! It was so bad I sent it back...will prob not go back

Me and my husband thought to try out this aunty pastos since we loved the one in waipahu, but we moved farther away from that one and stumbled upon this one. Have fun parking on the street, our waitress was literally breathing down our necks to make a decision. When we usually get the bread after our drinks she practically made us think they just weren't going to give us bread so we ordered an appetizer. As soon as we are done with it she gives us our bread. Are you serious? We normally put crushed red pepper in our olive oil, but there was none to he found on any table. So after being pestered 4 times to order we order.  As soon as we get our food and finished the bread she places the crushed red pepper down, and tells us to save room for dessert as we just get our entrees. I'd rather drive to waipahu...

We had salad, chicken parmesan, and 2 pizzas. The salads were mostly ice berg lettuce in chunks and not very appetizing. Our pizza was cold and inedible. We sent it back, and the second time around, it was a little better, but not much. What's up with the cardboard crust? The chicken parmesan came in 2 plates. The pasta was in a separate plate with parmesan cheese on top of it. We were sharing and when we dished out the pasta, the bottom of the plate was filled with water. The chicken and tomato sauce could have been quite tasty, except there was so much salt in it that, again, it was inedible. We ate part of it anyway, after all, this meal ended up costing us $70 (including tip) and we did not want to leave hungry. We won't be back to the restaurant at this location again.

I am absolutely convinced that Auntie Pasto's has the best lasagne in the entire world. I order mine with the meat & mushroom sauce and it is to die for. I read a recent review that someone was displeased with the lasagne, to each their own, but I believe Auntie Pasto's lasagne is absolutely divine!!!!  My husband and I eat there frequently and we haven't ventured to try another dish yet. We need to, but the lasagne is so hard to break away from and it's easily split between the two of us. It IS messy, but you don't eat lasagne with your hands do you? Either way you're going to use a fork, so it might as well be delicious and covered in their sauce.  Auntie Pasto's is a winner for sure. The staff is as friendly as can be. The restaurant has a very intimate layout. And I actually ENJOYED the fact that it was not freezing inside like most restaurants are. Top star establishment.  Mahalo!
They have good lunch values, and their bread is great

My wife and I went out last night for some pasta...being relatively new to the island, and driving by Auntie Pasto's daily..thought we would go in and give it a try.  We were seated at a nice table right by the window, and proceeded to order.  We had:  2 Glasses of House Red Wine (very sweet, and poor quality...it was like drinking Thunderbird from the convenience store, which I've only done once in High School.); 2 Caesar Salads, which were not more than romain lettuce with some store bought dressing...poor quality; EggPlant Paremesian which had way too much olive oil all over it, it was gross; Spaghetti and Meatballs, the meatballs were 80% bread crumbs with little to no spice.  Seating was good...then it went downhill.... House Red Wine was like drinking Thunderbird. McDonalds makes a better salad. Main Course too much olive oil; and meatballs should be renamed breadballs. Food was very poor quality. Service was like being served by a high school student.  Better off going to Olive Garden.  Auntie Pasto's is a lame duck.  Don't eat there if you can avoid it.
